      "Title": "Synopsis",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libsndfile is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Libsndfile is a C library for reading and writing files containing sampled sound such as MS Windows WAV and the Apple/SGI AIFF format through one standard library interface.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\nLibsndfile \u003c=1.2.2 contains a memory leak vulnerability in the mpeg_l3_encoder_init() function within the mpeg_l3_encode.c file.(CVE-2025-56226)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for libsndfile is now available for openEuler-24.03-LTS-SP1.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "Medium",
      "Title": "Severity",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "libsndfile",
      "Title": "Affected Component",
      "Type": "General"
    }
  ],
